    <!-- QUICK ANSWER -->
    <div class="quick-answer">
      <h3>Quick Answer</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>For a 200lb man over 40, 100g of protein per day is at or barely above the minimum — not an optimal target.</li>
        <li>Research puts the right range at 109–145g per day (1.2–1.6g per kilogram of bodyweight).</li>
        <li>The per-meal math is the bigger problem: 100g ÷ 4 meals = 25g per sitting — below the 30g threshold needed to trigger muscle protein synthesis after 40.</li>
        <li>100g is significantly better than the average intake of 50–70g — but it's still short of where muscle preservation actually happens.</li>
        <li>If you're training, the target moves to the higher end of that range.</li>
      </ul>
