        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mm-total">
        <span class="mm-total-label">Daily total</span>
        <span class="mm-total-num">~94g — 1 of 4 meals triggered MPS</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>That's the real picture. Even if you hit 100g on the day, the way most men distribute those grams means only one meal — dinner — actually crosses the threshold required to trigger muscle protein synthesis. The other three meals are metabolically inert from a muscle-building standpoint.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <p><strong>The fix isn't just eating more protein.</strong> It's restructuring when you eat it. Three or four meals each clearing 30g is far more effective for muscle preservation than hitting 100g total with one big dinner and three light meals. The <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/30-gram-protein-rule/">30-gram rule</a> exists exactly for this reason.</p>
    </div>

